{{Infobox person | name = Georges Jean | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1920|9|16|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Besançon]], [[France]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2011|12|19|1920|9|16|df=yes}} | death_place = | residence = | nationality = French | education = [[École normale supérieure de Saint-Cloud]] | occupation = [[Linguist]], [[semiotician]], [[poet]], [[children's literature]] writer | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | television = | spouse = | children = | awards = ‘Mention’ Budding Critic Award of [[Bologna Children's Book Fair]]<ref name=Premi /> | signature = | website = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} --> | footnotes = }}
'''Georges Jean''' (16 September 1920 – 19 December 2011<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lexpress.fr/culture/livre/le-poete-et-essayiste-georges-jean-est-decede_1064431.html |title=Le poète et essayiste Georges Jean est décédé |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2011-12-22 |magazine=[[L'Express]] |accessdate=2018-01-25 |language=fr}}</ref>) was a French poet and [[essay]]ist specializing in the fields of [[linguistics]], [[semiology]] and [[children's literature]].
== Career == Georges Jean was born in [[Besançon]], after studying philosophy, he entered the [[École normale supérieure de Saint-Cloud]]. He has devoted himself to teaching linguistics, poetry and semiology in the city [[Le Mans]] and the [[University of Maine (France)|University of Maine]] where he was professor of linguistics and semiology from 1967 to 1981.<ref>{{cite book |last=Jean |first=Georges |translator-last=Hawkes |translator-first=Sophie |date=1998 |title=Signs, Symbols, and Ciphers |series="[[Abrams Discoveries]]" series |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Discoveries_Signs_Symbols_and_Ciphers.html?id=bqEcAQAAIAAJ |location=New York |publisher=Harry N. Abrams |page=208 |isbn=9780810928428 |quote=About the author }}</ref> He was the leader of the {{lang|fr|Centre international poésie-enfance}} (‘International Poetry-Childhood Centre’), participated in the ministerial committee for theatrical creation. He was a teacher at the [[École nationale supérieure des sciences de l'information et des bibliothèques|École Nationale Supérieure des Bibliothèques]], and published more than 70 books including several collections of poems, essays and theories on poetry and pedagogy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.actualitte.com/article/monde-edition/a-91-ans-le-poete-georges-jean-s-est-eteint/29975 |title=A 91 ans, le poète Georges Jean s'est éteint |last=Solym |first=Clément |date=2011-12-22 |magazine={{ill|ActuaLitté|fr}} |accessdate=2018-01-25 |language=fr}}</ref>
His book {{lang|fr|Le plaisir des mots : Dictionnaire poétique illustré}} won the ‘Mention’ Budding Critic Award from [[Bologna Children's Book Fair]] in 1983.<ref name=Premi>{{cite web |url=https://www.bibliotecasalaborsa.it/ragazzi/bibliografie/9080 |title=Premi Grafici Fiera di Bologna 1983 |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=[[Biblioteca Salaborsa]] |publisher= |accessdate=2018-01-25 |language=it}}</ref> Another book {{lang|fr|L’écriture, mémoire des hommes|italic=yes}} (English edition – ''Writing: The Story of Alphabets and Scripts'') was one of the bestsellers in France,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Divers/Plus-sur-la-collection/Decouvertes-Gallimard/(sourcenode)/116085 |title=Collection Découvertes Gallimard |publisher=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |accessdate=2018-01-26 |language=fr}}</ref> and has been translated into 21 languages.
== Selected bibliography == * ''Le plaisir des mots : Dictionnaire poétique illustré'', collection « Découverte Cadet », série Hors série. Éditions Gallimard, 1982 * ''Dictionnaire des poètes et de la poésie'', Éditions Gallimard, 1983 * ''Bachelard, l’enfance et la pédagogie'', Éditions du Scarabée, 1983 * ''L’écriture, mémoire des hommes'', collection « [[Découvertes Gallimard]] » (nº 24), série Archéologie. Éditions Gallimard, 1987, new edition in 2007<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gallimard.fr/Catalogue/GALLIMARD/Decouvertes-Gallimard/Decouvertes-Gallimard/Archeologie/L-ecriture-memoire-des-hommes |title=''L’écriture, mémoire des hommes'', collection Découvertes Gallimard (n° 24) |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |publisher=[[Éditions Gallimard]] |language=fr |accessdate=2018-01-25 |quote=}}</ref> (translated into 21 languages with a total of 24 international editions) ** US edition – ''Writing: The Story of Alphabets and Scripts'', "[[Abrams Discoveries]]" series. Harry N. Abrams, 1992 ** UK edition – ''Writing: The Story of Alphabets and Scripts'', ‘[[New Horizons (Thames & Hudson)|New Horizons]]’ series. Thames & Hudson, 1992 * ''Langage de signes : L’écriture et son double'', collection « Découvertes Gallimard » (nº 67), série Archéologie. Éditions Gallimard, 1989 ** U.S. edition – ''Signs, Symbols, and Ciphers'', "Abrams Discoveries" series. Harry N. Abrams, 1998 ** UK edition – ''Signs, Symbols and Ciphers: Decoding the Message'', ‘New Horizons’ series. Thames & Hudson, 1999 * ''Voyages en Utopie'', collection « Découvertes Gallimard » (nº 200), série Littératures. Éditions Gallimard, 1994
